Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Systems Specialist Toronto , ON Description Permanent, full-time position – Toronto, ON If you’re a talented administrator with knowledge of library processes and applications, you’ll welcome this opportunity to act as a subject matter expert within the Library and Learning Resources Department and across the Toronto District School Board (TDSB). Reporting to the Systems Librarian, you will assist in the organization and day-to-day technical operational procedures of the library automation system and related applications to support the department and all TDSB library sites, as well as provide subject matter expertise and tier 2 technical support for the Integrated Library System (ILS) and the Library Help Desk. As a Library Systems Specialist, you will also assist in the creation and analysis of statistics from library processes and applications, develop and assess library system training for Teacher Librarians and Library Learning Resources staff, and provide guidance and direction to the Systems Technicians. PRIMARY DUTIES More specifically, as a Library Systems Specialist, you will: Analyse ongoing issues and identify solutions within the daily management and maintenance of the Integrated Library System (ILS) software;Assist with the strategic planning, including architecture changes and e-resource integration, of the Integrated Library System;Plan and test software updates of the Integrated Library System, including incident resolution and recommendations for enhancement requests;Assist Teacher Librarians with library systems maintenance and other library tasks, as determined by the Systems Librarian;Provide guidance, direction and training to Systems Technicians;Provide training, support and tier 2 technical problem resolution to the Library Help Desk; Create and maintain the operational policies and procedures manual;Create social media content for internal and external platforms;Establish, maintain and analyze data from the ServiceNow application to track workflow and develop recommendations for improving the Library Learning Resources service;Collect and analyze data on the Integrated Library System (ILS) and the Library Help Desk;Plan, develop and assess library automation training sessions for Teacher Librarian and Library Learning Resources staff;Act as a technical lead for Resource Fairs and other events;Liaise with IT and vendors to ensure ongoing support for the Integrated Library systems;Maintain an awareness of new library automation trends and developments in order to improve service and create efficiencies within the department, including research and participation in the evaluation on new products;Perform other duties, as assigned. QUALIFICATIONS To take on the role of Library Systems Specialist, you must have: A two (2)-year Library and Information Technician Diploma with three (3) years of experience working with Integrated Library Systems, or an equivalent combination of education and experience;In-depth knowledge of Integrated Library Systems;Proficiency in derived and original cataloguing;Knowledge of, and experience in, HTML coding;Demonstrated analytical, technical, diagnostic and problem-solving skills;The ability to successfully analyze and interpret user needs, technical and otherwise, and find solutions;Knowledge of related Board and Ministry of Education policies and procedures;Strong research and report-writing skills;Strong communication (oral/written) and interpersonal skills, with a strong customer service focus;Strong organizational and time management skills and the ability to meet deadlines;The ability to provide direction and guidance to staff, and proven team-building skills;The ability to conduct training sessions and assist staff; andProficient computer skills, which include Integrated Library Systems, Google Suite, Outlook, Web 2.0 tools, social media, and database management. Wage Range: $37.44 – $44.23 per hour This CUPE Local 4400 permanent position, located at 3 Tippett Road, involves occasional travel and requires the ability to lift and carry boxes/equipment weighing up to 20 kilograms. Please submit a detailed resume and covering letter as one file in PDF format, and include all relevant documents in your submission, by 4:30 p.m., November 1, 2023, quoting competition #CUPE C-23-0254UE in the subject line, to: Application.Submission@tdsb.on.ca Information regarding Wheelchair accessibility is available online. Only applicants selected for an interview will be contacted. Applications will not be acknowledged in writing. The Toronto District School Board is deeply committed to promoting Truth, Reconciliation and the rights of Indigenous peoples, Human Rights, Equity and Anti-Racism, and the elimination of Oppressive Practices, in our schools, our workplace and in the communities we serve. We strongly encourage applications from all individuals including those with varied lived experiences that can contribute to the diversification of the workforce at TDSB. We strive to meet the accommodation needs of persons with disabilities. Applicants are encouraged to make their needs for accommodation known in advance during the application process. The TDSB follows a hybrid work structure where some employees may be able to work remotely at times, based on operational requirements. Please refer to Policy P103 &lt;https://www.tdsb.on.ca/About-Us/Detail/docId/2277&gt;, Flexible Working Arrangements for more information. Compensation $37.44 – $44.23 per hour Closes: 1 November, 2023 Toronto District School Board Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
