earch strategy/interview techniques and programming. 8. Demonstrated knowledge of public library resources and services. 9. In depth understanding of automated library systems and a demonstrated proficiency in the use of a variety of technologies. 10. Demonstrated proficiency and interest in using a variety of digital devices. 11. Ability to carry out job functions with flexibility, creativity and initiative. 12. Demonstrated proficiency in Microsoft Office. 13. Strong organizational skills. Requirements Top of Form 1. Master's Degree in Library Science from an ALA accredited library school or equivalent library degree. 2. Management certificate from a recognized institution, or equivalent. 3. Minimum of four years experience working as a Librarian, including 2 years experience in a supervisory role and 2 years experience in library operations. 4. Valid B.C. Driver's Licence (minimum level ‘N’). 5. Criminal Record Check is required. Additional Information Those selected for an interview will be required to give a 10 minute presentation on an assigned topic Valid B. C. Drivers licence (minimum level ‘N’) is required Fraser Valley Regional Library is committed to maintaining a diverse and inclusive workplace and recognizes that a working environment that encourages input from all perspectives can only enhance our services to the public. We invite candidates who bring a diversity of thought, skills, and experiences to apply and thank you in advance for your interest and contributions. To apply click on the link below:CLICK HERE Compensation Min 39.47/Hour - Max: 46.23 /Hour Closes: 26 October, 2023 Fraser Valley Regional Library Abbotsford , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
