Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Director, Humber Libraries Etobicoke , ON Description Find Your Spot at Humber:At Humber, our career paths open up a world of infinite possibilities for you to explore. People are at the heart of the Humber experience. Here, every day we work shoulder to shoulder to deliver excellence, and in doing so, we redefine what it means to be a leader in polytechnic education. Humber employees are a diverse group of committed, caring and fun-loving people. Humber College Institute of Technology and Advanced Learning, one of Canada’s leading postsecondary institutions, offers a combination of theoretical learning and hands on experience and meets its vision of transforming postsecondary education through global and polytechnic leadership.Humber’s Centres of Innovation and Entrepreneurship will integrate applied research into program curricula and provide students with access to interdisciplinary and industry projects. We are seeking faculty who will provide students with an exceptional learning experience as we immerse our students in experiential learning and programs that empower them to think critically, make bold choices and become leaders of change. We take finding and growing the right talent very seriously. We strive to find and nurture extraordinary employees who bring their best each day. If you are interested in working in higher education and are looking to contribute to the largest polytechnic College in Ontario, as we shape the future of our students and communities, here is your opportunity to join our team. Job DetailsPosition Title: Director, Humber LibrariesStatus: Full TimeDepartment: LibrariesCampus/Location: North Campus, In PersonSalary Hiring Range: $130,000 - $165,000What you will do: Reporting to the Vice President, Students and Institutional Planning, the Director, Humber Libraries leads both Humber and University of Guelph-Humber library services in an integrated manner, and is responsible for comprehensive Library and Learning Commons operations in five locations across three campuses serving over 30,000 students. The Director is also responsible to develop and operationalize a vision and implement strategies that support Humber’s unique polytechnic brand of education, by connecting the Libraries’ mandate with institutional priorities and plans (Strategic, Academic, Digital and Divisional). Additionally, the Director is responsible for the administration of the University of Guelph-Humber (UoGH) Library services in partnership with the University of Guelph Library; support for UoGH program and curriculum reviews and sitting on UoGH committees.The Director is responsible for the leadership of library services through the development of information resources, collections, services and spaces and through the management of administrators, faculty and staff, budgets, facilities, and strategic and business plans. Specific responsibilities include:Working in partnership with Humber’s six Faculties, the incumbent oversees the selection, licensing, management and preservation of print and electronic resources, institutes innovative approaches to the development of academic supports for all modes of instruction delivery (in-class, hybrid and online), and ensures that the Library’s information resources are coordinated with academic programs in support of curriculum needs, as well as teaching, learning and research excellence. The Director, Humber Libraries coordinates and advises senior administration on issues pertaining to copyright both within the Library and across Humber and collaborates with other divisional leaders to develop and implement academic support services. The quality of the services and resources being developed and delivered by the Libraries have a significant impact on the college’s program review process and PEQAB audits and the retention and success of Humber and UGH students. The Director, Libraries oversees the Idea Lab which is designed to support digital fluency at the College and the University. The Idea Lab has four components: studio spaces, workshops, online resources, and student supports. Additionally, the Director, Libraries is responsible for the development, growth and operation of Humber Archives, which serve as the institutional memory of the College by identifying, preserving, and making available for use the documentary heritage of the College.The Director also provides leadership in consortia and cooperative activities with other colleges and institutions across the province. In addition, the Director remains current on trends and adopts or shares best practices in order to manage facilities, technologies and instructional assistance that reflects the changing learning and service needs of our students and faculty. The Director is also a member of the Students and Institutional Planning Leadership team and Humber’s Academic and Administrative Leadership Forum and is responsible for working in partnership with Information Technology Services and Facilities to build and implement a vision and mandate for collaborative Library and Learning Commons services and spaces at all campus locations. What you bring to the role: Education The successful candidate will hold a Master of Library Science or Master of Library and Information Science Degree from a university program accredited by the American Library Association or officially assessed as equivalent by a body such as the Comparative Education Service at the University of Toronto. Experience &amp; Skills The incumbent will have a minimum of nine years of progressive experience, along with sound knowledge of integrated Library Systems, Web 2.0 technology, advanced knowledge of Library and information databases; and Internet applications in an educational setting. Knowledge of and ability to leverage evolving educational technologies is critical. Direct / Technical / Leadership: Managerial expertise Ability to launch major new directions while maintaining current operations. Sound knowledge of information technologies and their applications in libraries Ability to use the Internet as a research and resource tool and to evaluate the quality of electronic resources for library use. Knowledge of curriculum development and delivery to develop programs and services that support academic success and information literacy. Other (“soft” skills): Excellent human relations skills Strong oral and written communication skills A commitment to working in a collaborative environment Ability to multi-task a variety of administrative responsibilities and projects The Director is a senior leader of a large department with multiple locations. This position involves continuous administration, evaluation, problem-solving, planning, budgeting, negotiating, and both internal and external liaising. The incumbent requires strong interpersonal, conflict resolution, and problem-solving skills, advanced computer knowledge and skills. Advanced research, written and oral communication and presentation skills are required. Overall understanding of the operation and structure of academic libraries and a vision for future directions of library and learning services and resources is a must. Knowledge of AODA and Copyright legislation to ensure that the Libraries and Learning Commons are meeting compliance around federal and provincial legislation is also required. What’s In it for you? • An opportunity to have an impact with a post-secondary institution, poised to do great things. • Diverse, hard-working, committed team of people who care about each other. • Tools and technology that will allow you to succeed at your job. • Amazing perks • Highly supportive work culture At Humber College we don’t just accept difference — we celebrate it! Experience comes in many forms, skills are transferable, and a progressive mindset goes a long way at Humber. If your experience is close to what we’re looking for, consider applying and tell us why you are a great candidate for this job. Find your Spot at Humber! We thank you for your interest in working with Humber College. Only applicants selected for an interview will be contacted. Consideration for Support Staff and Academic positions will be given to internal employees in accordance with the respective Collective Agreements. Equity, Diversity and Inclusion Humber College is committed to a workforce that reflects the diversity of our students and our city. We actively seek Indigenous Peoples and individuals from equity-deserving groups with demonstrated skills and knowledge to deal with all aspects of equity, diversity and inclusion in a post-secondary environment.Accommodation Humber College is committed to accommodating applicants with disabilities throughout the hiring process, in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). Our HR Generalists will work with applicants requesting accommodations at any stage of the hiring process. This document is available in alternate formats upon request. Anti-Discrimination Statement At Humber College, all forms of discrimination and harassment are prohibited. Students and employees have the right to study, live and work in an environment that is free from discrimination and harassment. If you need assistance on concerns related to discrimination and harassment, please contact the Centre for Human Rights, Equity and Inclusion http://hrs.humber.ca/human-rights-equity-diversity... or the Office of Student Conduct at studentconduct@humber.ca Compensation $130,000 - $165,000 Closes: 31 October, 2023 Humber College Etobicoke , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
