Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Project Coordinator Assistant Toronto , ON Description Position Profile: Project coordinator AssistantReports To: Project Coordinator, Accessible Reading and TechnologyCELA is a national not for profit organization that offers accessible reading services to people with print disabilities in Canada through member public libraries. CELA produces and distributes accessible books in both digital and physical formats, including braille, audiobooks and accessible ebooks. CELA’s collection currently provides access to over to 1,000,000 titles.CELA seeks a Project Coordinator Assistant for a term contract (December 1, 2023 – March 31, 2024).Reporting to the Project Coordinator, Accessible Reading and Technology, this role will coordinate testing and documentation of new smart speaker (i.e. Alexa) skills for audiobooks, helping to ensure that the project meets its objectives and milestones. This project will expand service options for audiobooks using newer technology. This is an exciting opportunity to have a positive effect on library services and the lives of readers across the country as part of an energetic, supportive, and dynamic team. This position is a virtual office opportunity and we welcome applicants from across Canada. Scope and Summary of Primary Responsibilities Contribute to overall project plans and monitor progress to key milestones;Develop testing plan for English and French smart speaker skills Lead testing process and provide direction and support to CELA staff contributing to smart speaker skill testing;Compile feedback and track issues identified; Coordinate the creation of documentation for staff and users in French and English;Work collaboratively with staff, contractors, and external stakeholders ensuring that work is coordinated effectively and information is shared;Identify and manage risks and dependencies, provide recommendations to address problems and reach expected results.Competencies and Qualifications University degree or equivalent combination of education and experience;Excellent written and oral communication skills in English; ability to read, write, and speak French required;Lived experience with a print disability as defined by the Canadian Copyright Act is a definite asset; Detail-oriented and self-directed;Experience with quality assurance testing and application development lifecycle highly desirable;Ability to work collaboratively and positively with individuals and groups in a distributed work environment and as part of a diverse team;Strong technology skills and ability to use standard office software (e.g. Excel, Word) essential; knowledge of assistive technology and digital accessibility highly desirable;Commitment to improving the accessibility of public library collections and services across Canada.Work Environment This is a virtual office opportunity, and the successful candidate will supply their own home office, computer, and reliable internet accessThis position is envisioned as a fixed-term service contract (December 1, 2023 – March 31, 2024). Position is for 10 hours per week.Salary: $30/hr.Reports To: Project Coordinator, Accessible Reading and Technology, CELA How to apply Please send a copy of your resumé with a cover letter (pdf or word) to jobs@celalibrary.ca, clearly indicating the position you are applying for to the attention of Holly Pickering by October 30, 2023 by 11:59 pm ET.CELA hires on the basis of merit. We are committed to the principle of equity in employment. We welcome diversity and encourage applications from visible minority group members, women, Indigenous persons, persons with disabilities, persons of minority sexual orientations and gender identities, and others with the skills and knowledge to productively engage with diverse communities. All qualified candidates are encouraged to apply; however, Canadians and permanent residents will be given priority. Compensation $30 hourly Closes: 30 October, 2023 Centre for Equitable Library Access Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
