Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Part-time Library Technician Barrie , ON Description Located in Owen Sound and reporting to the Operations Manager, the incumbent is responsible for providing a broad range of services within the library that support teaching and learning as well as the strategic priorities of Georgian College and Libraries and Academic Success. Specific duties include, but are not limited to: Delivering information and reference services to Georgian students and faculty (including university partnership students, alumni and guests) across all academic program areas, online and in-person through a variety of platforms (email, chat functions, video chat) Designing search strategies to support the Georgian community’s information queries, facilitating reference interviews, and retrieving appropriate resources from information sources Responding to student or faculty research questions from Georgian and other Ontario colleges through askON (a collaboration of Ontario college libraries that provides real-time, interactive chat). Understanding consortia service policy and procedure; navigating unfamiliar college websites, search tools, and resources to provide advanced information and reference services Incorporating digital tools to engage and support student learning within the reference interaction. Tools include, screen casting and image creation to better portray database use and functions Troubleshooting basic database issues and report instances of technical difficulties to the appropriate staff member or department Conducting library workshops (in person and online) to academic program areas promoting of Library and Academic Success services Evaluating effectiveness of orientations via various methods in consultation with Faculty Librarian(s) and Operations Manager, to improve student learning experiences Assisting in the development of tutorials and pathfinders in collaboration with Faculty Librarian(s) Assisting with developing and maintaining library collections Preparing collection profiles and online subject LibGuides Providing Interlibrary Loan (ILL) services to students and faculty; facilitating broad access to resources beyond the collections available from Georgian Libraries; searching for and locating materials held at other libraries, and communicating with other college and university ILL departments to secure resources either through the mail or electronically Maintaining currency and knowledge about copyright information and Georgian Copyright Policy (AD-019) Investigating new library service initiatives, digital tools, and emerging technologies Using general application software for databases, documents, presentations and spreadsheets Maintaining tracking systems for qualitative and quantitative data (gathering, compiling, and summarizing data related to library services) Performing circulation transactions using an automated integrated Library Services Platform, , including registering clients, signing materials in and out and placing holds Participating in Library and Academic Success promotion activities, including social media, and college orientation events Onboarding new Library Technician team members by job shadowing and demonstrating practices and policies Providing back-up for Customer Service deskQUALIFICATIONS: Successfully completed a two-year postsecondary diploma in a relevant field of study that may include, but is not limited to Library and Information Technician A minimum of two years’ experience in an academic learning environment performing duties to support the teaching, research, and learning of students and faculty; understanding the academic cycle and the corresponding information needs of the campus community Experience working in a library setting providing research services in a variety of subject areas, library orientations, collections management, and circulation preferred Advanced computer skills and experience with:Subscription databasesLibGuides (or equivalent) application softwareSocial media (Twitter, Facebook, YouTube, etc.)Online tutorial and video developmentScreen sharing and screen capture softwareMicrosoft Office Suite (Word, excel, PowerPoint, etc.)AODA and web related standards and guidelines Proven communication (oral and written) and interpersonal skills Demonstrated customer service experience with the ability to problem solve Ability to work independently and within a team environment Demonstrated organizational and time management skills with attention to detail Ability to work non-traditional hours (evening and weekends) Experience in an academic library and cataloguing are assets Experience with a student information system (i.e. Banner) and or a learning management system (i.e. Blackboard) is an assetGeorgian College supports diversity, equity and a workplace free from harassment and discrimination and is committed to an inclusive, barrier-free environment. We invite applications from all qualified candidates and actively encourage applications from members of groups with historical and/or current barriers to equity, including, but not limited to persons of Aboriginal ancestry, members of visible minorities, persons with disabilities, women and members of the 2SLGBTQ+ community. If you are contacted to participate in the interview, please advise the coordinator of any accommodations needed with respect to any materials or processes used to ensure you have access to a fair and equitable process.Alternate formats will be provided upon request throughout the recruitment and selection process.Georgian College has introduced FLEX Work for some positions. This position is currently eligible for Hybrid Work. FLEX Work agreements will be determined between the employee and manager when employment commences and may change in accordance with the FLEX Work guidelines. All employees are required to permanently reside in the province of Ontario.APPLY NOW:To be considered for this position, please visit our website at www.GeorgianCollege.ca and apply by navigating to About Us and then to Career Opportunities.Applications for this position must be received by 11:59 p.m. November 12, 2023. While we thank all applicants, only those contacted for an interview will be acknowledged. Compensation $21.77 - $28.88 Closes: 12 November, 2023 Georgian College Barrie , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
