Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Communications and Member Engagement Coordinator Vancouver , BC Description Position: Communications and Member Engagement CoordinatorOrganization: BC Libraries CooperativeLocation: Remote from anywhere in Western Canada with access to high-speed internetType of position: Full-time (35 hours/week), 3-year term, with possibility of extension. We are open to discussions of a 0.8FTE arrangement as well (28 hours/week.Compensation: $65,000-$77,000 FTE, depending on experienceClosing date: Sunday October 22, 2023 at midnight Pacific TimeAnticipated start date: January 2024ABOUT US The BC Libraries Cooperative (BCLC) is a mission-driven non-profit cooperative that helps libraries help people.Our 200+ members include public and post-secondary libraries and institutions across Canada. We provide libraries and related organizations with the services, cost savings, and support they need to do great work in their communities. We provide several online services for our members which include a focus on using open-source technology and systems, as well as expanding work in the field of accessible reading for inclusion of people in Canada with print disabilities.BCLC has a distributed workforce of over 44 people working across three time zones.For a detailed overview of our work at the BCLC please see: https://bc.libraries.coop/about/ABOUT THE ROLE This new role will work closely with the Executive Director and the Co-op's Management team to lead the development and implementation of a communications and member engagement strategy. The role will incorporate some current member engagement and communications components and combine them into an overall strategy and approach.External elements of the roleLead the development and implementation of a communications and member engagement strategy, which will include ways of telling the story of the Co-op's work in support of our membership. The communications strategy will include outreach to different stakeholder groups including members, funders and other stakeholders.Lead the development and implementation of a member engagement strategy that provides opportunities for members to regularly share feedback on the services and support the Co-op provides and share analysis of member feedback with management to assist in improving member relations.Work with relevant Co-op staff to centralize reporting on and analysis of, Co-op training offerings and gaps.Help develop new educational offerings for the membership.Where appropriate, incorporate EDI, accessibility, and member engagement elements into strategies.Manage the development, distribution, and maintenance of all print and electronic collateral including, but not limited to, the annual report, newsletters, brochures, and BCLC website, and work with staff to maintain consistent communications across all recommended methods, I.e. website, email, newsletters, social media, etc.Internal elements of the roleLead and help maintain internal communications strategy and processes including administrative intra and extranet designs.Oversee and coordinate an accessible documents strategy for co-op documents and processes.Take the lead on coordinating the Co-op's Annual General Meeting planning process and work with other staff on the creation ofreports.Under direction of the Management team and in collaboration with service teams, take a key role in coordinating and implementing the Co-op's accessibility plan and activities.SKILLS, QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE REQUIRED Required skills and experienceMinimum two years of experience in marketing, social media, content, digital, PR, or a related field —Strong writing and verbal communications skills, including experience using plain language to communicate with non-technical audiences.Experience and facility working with social media and content management systems.Experience with incorporating accessibility considerations into communications, including the creation of accessible documents and social media posts – or the willingness and ability to learn these skills and processes (the Co-op will also provide additional training in this area).Experience using graphic design software, and comfort with exploring and learning new systems and tools.Strong command of the English language (written and spoken).Not required, but considered an asset:Previous experience in a library setting.Experience working with a member-driven organization and developing engagement strategies.Knowledge on accessibility and the creation of accessible documents and social media posts is a highly valued asset, (the co-op will also provide training in this area).ADDITIONAL SKILLS AND ABILITIES REQUIRED TO PERFORM DUTIESThe role requires a strong customer service attitude when communicating with member library staff, vendors, and other partner organizations. The ideal candidate will also have a strong commitment to the values and approaches that inform the Co-op’s work.Collaboration - Ability to work collaboratively with staff, members, and external service providers, support effective team processes and establish positive relationships within and outside of the organization.Integrity -Good judgement, ethics, and awareness of privacy and security requirements.Communication – Strong interpersonal and communication skills (written, oral).Time Management - Ability to effectively manage time and priorities in a dynamic remote work environment.COMPENSATION PACKAGE This is a 3-year term position, with the possibility of extension, subject to funding.This is a full-time remote position (35 hours per week). The compensation range is $65,000-$77,000 annually, depending on experience.While the candidate will work primarily regular business hours Monday-Friday, there may be some occasional evening and weekend hours required for some projects.Co-op staff work remotely, from home.We have a Bring Your Own Device environment, with an allowance of $75/month to cover home office requirements. Access to high-speed internet is a requirement.The successful candidate will be enrolled in the Municipal Pension Plan, a defined benefit pension plan.BCLC has family friendly workplace policies including a generous annual vacation allotment, which starts at 20 days per year, with additional days accruing with years of service, a week’s closure in late December, 10 personal days a year, and a work culture that supports staff well-being.After a 90-day holdback period, there is enrolment in an employer-paid extended medical and dental package for employees and their dependants that includes a health spending account.The Co-op committed to creating a diverse, equitable and inclusive workforce. We encourage women, people of Indigenous ancestry, people of colour, 2SLGBTQQIA+ individuals, people with disabilities and members of other equity-deserving groups to apply for careers with our organization.APPLICATION PROCESS Interested applicants should submit their cover letter and resume to office@bc.libraries.coop.When submitting your consolidated application, please name and save your attachment with your first and last name in the title, such as: “FirstnameLastname CommunicationsCoordinator.pdf”Only those candidates who are short-listed will be contacted. Interviews will be held via video conference in mid-late November with an anticipated start date in December/January.The posting is also available at: to add linkThe application deadline is Sunday October 22, 2023, at midnight Pacific Time. Compensation $65,000-$77,000 FTE, depending on experience Closes: 22 October, 2023 BC Libraries Cooperative Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
